snippet.textDisplay:
If 9 million are dying every year imagine what the figures will be like in future.
Air Pollution usually doesn't kill a person overnight but takes years to develop and spread.
More pollutants are coming on the market every day and combined with many more chemicals in food and water the future doesn't look bright for those not able to actively pursue other alternatives.
